Bien que la souris photographe ne soit pas de la partie, ce petit moment privilégié avec Marine a été conservé pour mon plus grand plaisir 🥰🥰🥰
J’ai toujours apprécié passer du temps avec elle avant de l’amener au Village des Animaux... C’est un personnage tellement attachant que j’ai véritablement un mal fou à me séparer d’elle : j’adore son professionnalisme au Jeu dans le Vent, son enthousiasme quand on creuse des trous, ses petites leçons de morale quand on fouille dans les placards ou quand on s’attaque à une poule (même si cela l’amuse aussi au bout d’un moment 😄) et bien d’autres choses. Je pouvais rester des heures sur la place du Village des Mouettes rien que pour l’écouter chanter sa douce mélodie, espérant retarder l’échéance le plus possible.
Son rêve était aussi pur qu’elle, j’aurais souhaité qu’il existe un autre moyen de le réaliser... ✨🌊✨

caption.text:
I may be a little late to the party, but now that my setup is back together, I had to jump in on the #shmupsareshooters tag that @turbothunder16 started last week! I may not have the biggest collection of shooters at the moment, but I've been growing to really love the genre over the past couple of years! -
-
Galactic Attack on the Sega Saturn is the first game that I actively sought out after finally getting a Saturn a few years ago, and I'm glad I did! It's hard to beat in terms of affordability and accessibility, especially compared to most others on the Saturn. And while it may not be the "best" shooter, I have a ton of fun playing it, and I think it was a great place to start! -
-

caption.text: Red Dead Redemption 2 is one of the many games on my backlog 👾 Currently working on Dark Souls III it’s so fun and so difficult! Also playing: Diablo 3, grinding in Neverwinter, TLOZ: Links Awakening and all of the other new games that are coming out 🥺 it doesn’t help that I get distracted by everything in games and explore wayyy to much. If a game can be completed in 12 hours it takes me 40 😭💀 So games like these that take 50-80+ hours to complete is going to be a looong journey for me, I’m really slow xD I’m also super slow with editing... so I may be behind on my YT stream highlights for a while 😅 Planning on making one for my Zelda & Dark Souls 3 playthrough tho! If you’d like to subscribe to my YouTube the link is in my bio 🥰

🔥📖🔥Something I’ve never attempted and always wanted to do was Paper Mario: The Thousand Year Door Hard Mode, and it turns out you don’t even need a hack or mod for the game to do so (although there are many). Simply pick up the Double Pain badge for 36 coins after chapter 1 from Charlieton in Rogueport’s square and apply it for literally zero badge points and instantly baddies will deal double damage to Mario!! Loving my run of it so far and it has certainly increased the intensity and changied things up in an interesting way for an old favorite game of mine, and needless to say some ridiculously tight fights now occur in spades!!

This month last year is what started me thinking down my current path of focusing on Cosplay items for my business.  A friend of mine is always doing something for halloween.  He was struggling to create a Thanos helmet using paper.  2 days before Halloween I asked if he’d like my help.  I went home that night and sculpted this Thanos helmet in VR and started it printing.  The next day I was able to give it to him and here is the final result after he painted it.  It wasn’t perfect but solidified my interest in this type of art.
